“And God took a handful of southerly wind, blew his breath over it and created the horse.” – Bedouin legend “Funny things, horses. Dirty, dangerous, greedy beasts, they get into your blood like a virus, and once you’ve got it there’s no cure.” – UK stable hand Susan Gallier “There is no better buzz than racing – it gives me a bigger kick than football when I have a winner.” – Ex-footballer Kevin Keegan “I was more nervous than when I played before 55,000 at Old Trafford.” – Ex-footballer Mick Quinn on sending out his first winner as a trainer...